{
  "stem": "14897.4",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Half-- we were about 250, and they were about 350 people.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So 600 people remained.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "We were, to the end, a somewhat privileged group, I don't think for any reason other than sort of administrative continuity.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "The Germans were always obsessed with formality, even in a camp.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "For example, when people died, my father, who had to make out the death certificate, would have to write that they had a heart attack, you know, or something.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Even if you knew that they died of starvations, you were not allowed to write anything like that.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "They kept records.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He was the camp doctor in our group.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You see, at the beginning, there were several doctors in the group.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Later on, there were just two.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my father was selected by the Germans to be the representative of-- of our group.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And what made us a select group is that we never worked.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And this had pluses and minuses.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The pluses definitely were more important, because it meant, number one, that we did not use up as much energy.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The food that they gave us was very scant.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We received some ersatz coffee in the morning, a soup in the middle of the day, a quart of soup, which was almost invariably turnip soap with little pieces of fish sometimes floating and little pieces of potato, and more coffee in the evening.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And once or twice a week, bread soup in the evening, a horrible thing which tasted wonderful at the time.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And we also were a group, a mixed group, men and women together.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, at the beginning, we had to sleep separately.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
